The Kenya Library Association, Goethe-Institut and Jomo Kenyatta Foundation annually organise the Library of the Year Award. The Maktaba Award aims to recognise excellence in the provision of library and information services in the country. During this year s edition held on Friday at the National Musuems of Kenya s Louis Leakey Auditorium, KNLS Kisumu emerged as the overall winner.In attendance were Ministry of Education director Irreneous Kinara, Kopo Kopo finance director Peace Osangir, German Embassy head of cultural affairs Uwe Koppel and Amani Kibera founder Ben Ooko.